Business Brief -- Prime Motor Inns L.P.:
   Operating Partners
   Makes a Chapter 11 Filing
AMI, which owns and operates 16 hotels in Maryland,
Pennsylvania and Connecticut, said its senior lenders have
agreed in principle to defer past-due interest and principal,
to reduce the interest rate payable through 1994 and to
extend the maturity of existing loans. AMI has been in
default on its senior loan for several months.
   In addition, some lenders have agreed in principle to
provide as much as $14 million of additional financing for
improvements and refurbishment of the hotels and to fund
operations.
   AMI said it expects to emerge from its prepackaged
bankruptcy within 60 to 90 days. Under Chapter 11, a company
continues to operate but has court protection against
creditors' lawsuits.